    "content": "nullSales Performance Management\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Sales Performance Management\n Sales Planning\n Sales Planning Setup\n Data Sources Management\n Create a Sales Plan\n Segmentation\n Territory Planning\n Implementing Territory Planning\n Importing Data for Planning Territories\n Designing Strategic Territories\n Aligning Territories to Reach Leadership’s Goals\n Plan Territories for In-Person and Virtual Business\n Assigning Units Based on Rules and Criteria\n Considerations for Assigning Units Based on Rules\n Assign Units Based on Rules That You Define\n Distributing Units Based on Your Company’s Metrics\n Designing Territories with Visualizations Using Overlays\n Keeping Territories Running Smoothly\n Quota Planning\n Quota Attainment Planning\n Legacy Sales Planning\n Incentive Compensation Management\n Release Notes for Sales Performance Management\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALES PERFORMANCE MANAGEMENT\nAssign Units Based on Rules That You Define\n\nDistribute accounts to reps based on their areas of responsibility, such as industry, annual revenue, and number of employees. Fine-tune assignment rules and their criteria from Salesforce territory models and create any other rules that matter for your sales and service leadership in Territory Planning.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS\nAvailable in: both Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with Web Services API enabled\n\n\nUSER PERMISSIONS NEEDED\nTo customize settings:\tCustomize Application\nOpen an alignment whose units you want to assign using criteria in assignment rules.\nEdit an area. In Assignment Rules, click Add a Rule, and then add criteria for assigning accounts to the area’s owner.\nIf you assign boundaries to areas, Territory Planning generates boundary rules, which appear as assignment rules. If you remove boundary assignments, you also remove their corresponding generated boundary rules.\nSave your changes.\nAdd account rules and criteria for any other areas in the alignment.\nAssignment rules distribute the units to areas based on the criteria that you set.\nWhen you publish alignments to Sales Territories, you also publish your assignment rule updates and generated boundary rules for accounts.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
